node.text: @100humansnetflix Remember when I was shooting a show I couldn’t talk about? WELL HI I FINALLY CAN. ‘100 Humans’ premieres March 13 on Netflix. Social psychology, experiments, candor, and un-earned labcoats. Put it on your watch list now, kiddos. It’s a wild ride. Hosted alongside amazing comedians @zainabjohnson & @sammyobeid whoms I like a lot.

node.text: Last Saturday I married the Mayor of Babetown @jarrett_sleeper and one of my favorite moments was in the cluttered little bridal room afterward, signing the license with officiants @dailynrod & @milescooks and just knowing that after 10 years of loving this guy, we made it work and made a choice and committed to this big giant love and that our future would very soon involve cake. More pictures and stories to come if you want ‘em. (📷: @katmburns) #adecadetotheday

node.text: A pre-wedding dinner: Jarrett somehow manages to look like a male model while wearing a clip-on bowtie, and I’m wearing my great grandma Dell’s black & lace wedding dress, over 100 years old. Thank you so much for marrying my ass tomorrow @jarrett_sleeper and to his radiant mom @the.rose.woman for such a gorgeous evening. Any wedding day tips, especially for someone who doesn’t know how to attend a party without helping clear the dishes or make the drinks?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Alie Ward on July 07, 2021 tagging @alieward, @jarrett_sleeper, @simonegiertz, and @insta_gremmie.

node.text: Soooo, I’m getting hitched to my longtime crush and my dear friend @simonegiertz came over with a pizza and when I opened the box it was not a pizza but a hand-crafted family crest she’d made featuring 1) Gremmie as a griffon, wearing a jiu jitsu belt like @jarrett_sleeper 2) a bug 3) my feather collection 4) the motto Jarrett had mentioned that is the foundation of our relationship: patience and relentless optimism. As people with depression, ADHD and anxiety, that last one is hard. The world is pretty jagged and unsafe, BUT so many people are wonderful, and want to make things better for each other. Anyway, I love the life @jarrett_sleeper has given me, and @simonegiertz for being a friend who saw me instantly and who was immediately an ol’ pal. #alieandjearneedahashtag

node.text: A red conditioner stained my bangs ketchup for 6 months so I tried a color stripper last night and now I have a homemade orange-red ombré. Do I fix this or pretend it was intentional? Please note I ask this as a person wearing a backwards sweater and drinking from yesterday’s reused jack in the box cup that happened to match my hair so, so perfectly. Maybe just normalize my mistake by asking your stylist for the buttery jack

node.text: This is a post to brag that @blackforager, the world’s most beloved wild food enthusiast aka Alexis Nikole Nelson, IS ON @OLOGIES. SHE IS ON OLOGIES. She talks about knotweed, mugwort, giant hogweed, cow parsnips, morels, dandelions, secret persimmons, nontoxic berries, foraging in cities vs. forests and why it’s a radical & empowering act. WE LOVE HER SO MUCH WERE FREAKING OUT. #ForagingEcology episode is up wherever you get podcasts or go to the link in the @ologies bio. And follow @blackforager if you don’t. 🍀🌿💚🌾🌱 (📷: Credit: Columbus, OH-based photographer @racheljoybarehl)

Photo shared by Alie Ward on May 21, 2021 tagging @ologies, and @blackforager. May be an image of text that says 'alie ward Mustard gossip. Knotweed recipes. Cow parsnips. Serviceberry appreciation. Hogweed warnings. Dead man's fingers. The incredibly knowledgeable and entertaining Alexis Nikole Nelson a.k.a. @BlackForager walks us through Foraging Ecology with a ginormous bushel of tips & tricks for finding edibles at all times of the year, from blossoms to fungus. Belly up for some invasive snacks, elusive mushrooms, magnolia cookies, mugwort potatoes, violet cocktails, foraging guides, weed trivia and tips to avoid poisonous berries. Also: finding community, history, land stewardship and why foraging is important, empowering and quite tasty.'.

node.text: Thaaaank youuu to everyone who showed up for the first ever @ologies live show last night! I wasn’t sure if this would be a one-off but it was so fun to catch up with @volcano.jess last night and meet a bunch of you that I just may have to do it again with another past guest. In a yellow sweater. And a ball gown. Probably not the volcano hat though. Thoughts?

node.text: This week’s @ologies is #Biominerology & I just became aware of @beansofjohn’s work and WOW. It’s this episode in a nutshell/snail shell. Your new fave @biomineralogist @robertnulrich tells me all about how squishy babies make hard shells, how chalk is made up of skeletons, how a conch does not reflect your earblood noises, scientists putting cement on your teeth, why Florida wants to shred your feet, life in/out of the closet + more. Also now you know @beansofjohn is out there making this weird world weirder: a gift.

node.text: Happy Mamas’ Day to existing matriarchs of all species, future moms, hopeful moms, and moms who lost little ones. I’m in Connecticut taking a few days to visit @samantha.sleeper with Jarrett and in one day we’ve seen nests in all varieties, and gotten to watch Sam rearing a pretty cool little dude. Thanks for raising all these people, people. I recently poisoned my dog with cake (she’s fine) so I obviously don’t know how y’all do it with humans, but I respect it mightily. 💖
